title: Iran beach soccer edge Colombia in friendly match
description: TEHRAN – Iran beach soccer team defeated Colombia 3-2 in a friendly match on Friday.

title: Turkey: World’s silence on Gaza ‘complicity in genocide’
description: Turkish Foreign Minister Hakan Fidan has expressed concern over the world’s silence on Israel’s actions in Gaza, describing it as “complicity in genocide”.

title: Humanitarian organisation warns of ‘catastrophic consequences’ if Israel invades Rafah
description: Two weeks since the International Court of Justice (ICJ) ruling, the situation for civilians in Gaza has become even worse, according to humanitarian organisation Islamic Relief.

title: Israeli snipers kill 21 as displaced Palestinians trying to reach Nasser Hospital
description: Israeli snipers have killed at least 21 people in Khan Younis in the south of Gaza, where displaced Palestinians were gunned down trying to reach Nasser Hospital.

title: UN chief says world must ‘push to avoid’ Rafah tragedy
description: The United Nations chief is calling for a ceasefire in Gaza before “a gigantic tragedy” develops in Rafah if Israel attacks, Al Jazeera reported on Friday.

title: Iran FM flies to Beirut for high-level talks with Lebanese and resistance leaders
description: TEHRAN - Iran’s Foreign Minister Hossein Amir Abdollahian departed Tehran for Beirut to meet with “senior Lebanese officials and leaders of resistance groups”.

title: Protected areas rise 5.5 times after Islamic Revolution
description: TEHRAN – The number of protected areas under the supervision of the Department of Environment has increased 5.5 times after the 1979 Islamic Revolution.

title: Gaza death toll rises to 27,947
description: Gaza’s Health Ministry says the death toll from Israel’s aggression on the blockaded territory has risen to 27,947 since October 7, Al Jazeera reported.

title: DOE to combat SDSs in Sarakhs bordering Turkmenistan
description: TEHRAN – The Department of Environment is taking measures with the aim of dealing with sand and dust storms in Sarakhs County, near the border with Turkmenistan.

title: Saudi king replies to Iranian president’s message on Gaza
description: TEHRAN – Riyadh’s ambassador to Tehran has delivered a written message from the Saudi king in response to the Iranian president’s letter about the crisis in the Gaza Strip.

title: Launching smart crisis management systems on agenda
description: TEHRAN - Designing and launching comprehensive systems with various layers of data for smart management of natural disasters are on the agenda, Hossein Zafari, an official with the Crisis Management Organization, has said.

title: All warships will be forced to leave Red Sea, Yemen says
description: A ranking Yemeni official says foreign warships will eventually be forced to leave the strategic Red Sea.

title: Situation in Gaza is a tragedy for all humanity: Leader
description: TEHRAN – Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, the Leader of the Islamic Revolution, says the ongoing catastrophic incidents in the Gaza Strip are a tragedy for the Muslim world and the entire humanity.

title: Situation in Gaza is a tragedy for humanity: Ayatollah Khamenei
description: TEHRAN – Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, the Leader of the Islamic Revolution, says the ongoing catastrophic incidents in the Gaza Strip are a tragedy for the Muslim world and the entire humanity.

title: Hepatitis C elimination probable within 2-3 years: health ministry
description: TEHRAN – The ministry of health is planning to eradicate hepatitis C across the country within a period of 2 to 3 years.

title: Iran censures US killing of Iraqi anti-terror commander, calls it ‘state terrorism’
description: TEHRAN - Iran on Thursday denounced the American assassination of a senior Iraqi commander in the fight against terrorism and some other fellow resistance fighters against terrorists, calling the move a “terrorist act” by the U.S. administration “inside Iraq.”

title: Number of National Housing Movement units exceeds 2.1m
description: TEHRAN- The number of National Housing Movement units has exceeded 2.1 million throughout the country, Hadi Abbasi, the deputy Transport and Urban Development Minister for the housing and construction, announced.

title: Over 95% of Iran’s population enjoy natural gas
description: TEHRAN- Based on the released data, 95.54 percent of Iran’s population enjoys natural gas at the present.

title: Nearly 21m tons of basic goods imported in 10 months
description: TEHRAN- The Islamic Republic of Iran Customs Administration (IRICA) reported that 20.934 million tons of basic commodities worth $13.619 billion were imported to the country during the first ten months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 21, 2023-January 20, 2024).

title: New regulations set for medicinal plants export
description: TEHRAN- An official with Iran’s Agriculture Ministry announced that new regulations have been set for the export of medicinal plants.

title: Steel products export up 5.1% in 10 months on year
description: TEHRAN- Iran’s export of steel products rose 5.1 percent during the first ten months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 21, 2023-January 20, 2024), as compared to the same period of time in the past year, Bahram Sobhani, the chairman of the Iranian Steel Producers Association (ISPA), announced.
